# GitHub Runner Registration
#
# Preferred (default for fresh bootstraps): mint a 1h registration token via
#   gh api -X POST repos/paperwork-labs/paperwork/actions/runners/registration-token --jq '.token'
# and put it in RUNNER_TOKEN below. The runner persists its config to the named
# docker volume on first start; subsequent restarts do NOT need a fresh token.
#
# Alternative (only if you expect to wipe runner volumes and want auto-recovery):
# set ACCESS_TOKEN to a long-lived GitHub PAT with `repo` scope. Leave
# RUNNER_TOKEN unset in that case.
REPO_URL=https://github.com/paperwork-labs/paperwork
RUNNER_TOKEN=          # short-lived registration token (preferred)
# ACCESS_TOKEN=        # long-lived GitHub PAT, repo scope (alternative)
RUNNER_GROUP=default
